<?xml version="1.0"?>
<html>
  <problem>
    <title>CheckPoint: Energy in SHM</title>
    <p>
</p><br/> 
A block, attached to a spring, follows simple harmonic motion as shown in the diagram. 

    <br/>
    <img encrypturl="no" src="/static/problems/MIT/rayyan/check_points/Pictures/BK139.PNG" alt="BK139" texwrap="none"/>
    <br/>
    
      <p>
Which of the following statements about the energy of this system are true? In the options below, K stands for kinetic energy and U stands for potential energy. </p>
    
    <part loncapaid="11">
      <optionresponse texlayout="horizontal" max="14" randomize="no" loncapaid="12">
        <ul>
          <li>
            
              <p>K is directly proportional to the displacement from equilibrium</p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil1" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>K is inversely proportional to the displacement from equilibrium</p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil2" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>K is directly proportional to the square of the displacement from equilibrium</p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil3" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>U is directly proportional to the displacement from equilibrium</p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil4" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>U is inversely proportional to the displacement from equilibrium</p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil5" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>U is directly proportional to the square of the displacement from equilibrium</p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil6" options="('True','False')" correct="True">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>K is at a maximum when the acceleration is zero</p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil7" options="('True','False')" correct="True">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>K is at a minimum when U is at a maximum</p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil8" options="('True','False')" correct="True">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>U is at a maximum when the acceleration is at a maximum</p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil9" options="('True','False')" correct="True">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>U is at a minimum when the velocity is zero</p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil10" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>The sum (K+U) is directly proportional to the displacement from equilibrium</p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil11" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>The sum (K+U) is inversely proportional to the displacement from equilibrium</p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil12" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>The sum (K+U) is directly proportional to the acceleration</p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil13" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>The sum (K+U) is inversely proportional to the acceleration</p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil14" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </optionresponse>
    </part>
      </problem>
</html>
